      "span_text": "that the putative target for selection is an allele that reached to approximately 70% allele frequency in East Asia, but remain at 25% allele frequency in Europe ( Figure 4B ). Then, we used the simple formula detailed (15) in [CITATION_1] and estimated that it would take $580 and $160 thousand years under neutrality for that single haplotype to increase in allele frequency from 1/2N e in ancestral African population to 70% and 25% observed in Asia and Europe, respectively."
